race.comment: WARICA (2) came with a powerful run when narrowly beaten over 1150m at Devonport Synthetic. He'd won there prior and has a 2/5 winning record this course/distance. An in-form hoop replaces the apprentice and briefly freshened he's a decent chance to bounce. COOL HEART (4) presents third-up and rates a threat. She's been giving away starts but draws well and she has more up her sleeve. Pires will give her every chance. OHSHE'STROUBLE (5) has been freshened again and gets a key jockey switch to Darmanin replacing the 4kg apprentice. Led and just missed two back on the synthetic as favourite and she'll be in the finish putting her best foot forward. STARS IN THE NIGHT (6) resumes with a 2kg claim and will use the inside barrier. She's proven fresh and is good enough at best. Has trialled twice at Longford and the betting will be key with her.
